data.reddit:
Age: 19
Sex: Female
Height: 5’8
Weight: 140 
Race: White
Duration: Shortly after a bout of Mononucleosis and Strep Throat concurrently in September 2018 (10 months) 
No current medications 
No (other) existing medical issues

In September I had a bad case of mono, and also had a positive strep test, and missed a month of school. 
During a physical recently I told my doctor that I have not been feeling well. I get physically exhausted after menial tasks and have been getting dizzy when standing, sometimes falling or having “blackouts” in my vision. I have also had about 7 colds/flu symptom bouts in the 10 months since. She ordered many lab tests, results stated below. 

Abnormal test results: 

RBC, Auto 4.09 Mill/mcL
Standard 4.20-5.40 Mill/mcl

HGB 11.4 g/dL 
Standard 12.0-16.0 g/dL

MCHC 30.0 g/dL 
Standard 32.0-37.0 g/dL

RDW, Blood 15.5% 
Standard 11.5-14.5% 

Anion Gap 12 mEq/L 
Standard 3-11 mEq/L 

Vitamin D 17 ng/mL 
Standard 30-100 ng/mL 

Not abnormal (on the low end) , but my WBC AUTO was 4.5 x1000/mcL when the standard range is 4-11 x1000/mcL. My MCH level is 27.9 pg/cell when the standard is 27-35 pg/cell.

Normal: Creatinine, Lipid Panel, Alanine Aminotransferase, Electrolytes (besides Anion Gap), Fasting Glucose, Hemoglobin A1C, Thyroid Stimulating Hormone, Vitamin B-9, Vitamin B-12, Hematocrit, MCV, Platelets. 


A nurse finally contacted me today and prescribed me a 12 week vitamin d supplement, where I take one pill a week. Does the Vitamin D deficiency seem like the root cause? I can barely fathom how it is causing me this much trouble, and am pretty frustrated. Any help is appreciated so so much!
